  "encoding": "windows-1252",
  "html": "\n<div><center>\n<table bordercolor=\"#000080\">\n<tr>\n<td><font><img src=\"../images/R.gif\"/> <strong>On\n    the Rialto</strong></font><hr noshade=\"\"/>\n<p><font>Cf. Shakespeare, <em>The Merchant of Venice</em>: \"Signoir Antonio,\n    many a time and oft / In the Rialto you have rated me / about my moneys and my usances: /\n    Still I have borne it with a patient shrug\" (1.3.101-4)</font>. From his historical\n    perspective of his own image as a martyr, this is the one Bleistein selects to complement\n    Burbank's perception.</p>\n<p><font><em>reference topics</em></font></p>\n<table>\n<tr>\n<td>\"Burbank\" and the Rialto</td>\n<td><a href=\"Stones_JR.htm\"><img src=\"arrowry.gif\"/></a></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><a href=\"Shylock.htm\">Bleistein and Shylock</a></td>\n<td><a href=\"Stonesi_JR.htm\"><img src=\"arrowry.gif\"/></a></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Dramatic Rethoric in Burbank</td>\n<td><img src=\"arrowry.gif\"/></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Structural analysis</td>\n<td><img src=\"arrowry.gif\"/></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><a href=\"IMG_Rialto.htm\"><img src=\"pic.gif\"/> Canaletto's Rialto bridge</a></td>\n<td></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><a href=\"IMG_Rialto1988.htm\"><img src=\"pic.gif\"/> Rialto bridge, Venice 1988</a></td>\n<td></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><a href=\"Burbank_A.htm\"><font>back to \"Burbank\"</font></a></td>\n<td><a href=\"Burbank_A.htm\"><img src=\"arrowry.gif\"/></a></td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n</center></div>\n",
  "text": "On the Rialto Cf. Shakespeare, The Merchant of Venice : \"Signoir Antonio, many a time and oft / In the Rialto you have rated me / about my moneys and my usances: / Still I have borne it with a patient shrug\" (1.3.101-4) . From his historical perspective of his own image as a martyr, this is the one Bleistein selects to complement Burbank's perception. reference topics \"Burbank\" and the Rialto Bleistein and Shylock Dramatic Rethoric in Burbank Structural analysis Canaletto's Rialto bridge Rialto bridge, Venice 1988 back to \"Burbank\"",
